    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for the right or condition of complete dominion, title, or proprietary right to a real or other property as allowed by law. Ownership may be private, collective, or common. Ownership may be present even in the absence of possession.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
